Program: Outlook
Title: Spanish Museum of Ham
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbr5d
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
A visit to the museum of ham in Madrid, Spain plus a comparison of food conservation methods around the world. Also, the 'Song of Solomon' is read in celebration of Valentine's day. And, a consideration of the greatest inventions of the last 2000 years.